Probably cognate with {{cog|ojp|-}} verb {{ja-r|з”ҹгӮҶ|гҒҜгӮҶ|to [[sprout]], to [[grow]]}} вҶ’ modern {{ja-r|з”ҹгҒҲгӮӢ|гҒҜгҒҲгӮӢ}}, and with {{ja-r|зҫҪ|гҒҜ|[[feather]]; [[wing]]}}.

Suggested in some sources as possibly cognate with {{ja-r|жӯҜ|гҒҜ|[[tooth]]}}, from the way that both sprout and then later fall,<ref>{{R:Gogen Yurai Jiten|и‘үпјҸгҒҜ|ha}}</ref> and with {{ja-r|еҲғ|гҒҜ|[[blade]]}} from similarities in shape (cf. {{cog|en|blade}}). However, the pitch accent patterns are different; {{m|ja|и‘ү}} and {{m|ja|зҫҪ}} are both unaccented, while {{m|ja|жӯҜ}} and {{m|ja|еҲғ}} are both accented. This may reflect two disparate ''*pa'' roots in the ancient language.

First attested in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' of 712 {{CE}} with the phonetic spelling {{lang|ja|жіў}}.<ref name="KDJ"/>

Cognate with {{cog|ryu|и‘ү|tr=fДҒ}}.

